---
// 3. Compare - "other apps" vs Lingo7 Realty as a two-column comparison table.
---
<section class="compare" id="why">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section__title"><strong class="hero__hl">Study in your own language.</strong> Take the exam in&nbsp;English.</h2>
    <p class="section__subtitle"><strong class="hero__hl">You understand the material right away.</strong> Then the app helps you practice the questions until they feel&nbsp;easy.</p>

    <div class="compare__table">
      <div class="compare__colbg" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <div class="compare__hcell compare__hcell--old">
        <span class="compare__icon compare__icon--old">✕</span>
        <span class="compare__hlabel">Other apps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="compare__hcell compare__hcell--new">
        <span class="compare__icon compare__icon--new">✓</span>
        <span class="compare__hlabel">Lingo7 Realty</span>
      </div>

      <div class="compare__cell compare__cell--old">
        <strong>Everything in English</strong>
        <p>The book, the words, the questions, the answers, all in English. Your energy goes to the language, not the material.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="compare__cell compare__cell--new">
        <strong>Translation built in</strong>
        <p>Everything comes with a translation in your language. You understand it at once.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="compare__cell compare__cell--old">
        <strong>Too much to memorize</strong>
        <p>Hundreds of terms and questions. You cram one thing and forget another.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="compare__cell compare__cell--new">
        <strong>Cards that make it stick</strong>
        <p>The app brings each term back right before you forget it. A proven way to remember.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="compare__cell compare__cell--old">
        <strong>Every new word slows you down</strong>
        <p>You stop, you lose focus, and you learn more slowly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="compare__cell compare__cell--new">
        <strong>One simple flow</strong>
        <p>Question → translation → review, all in one place. The language stops getting in the way.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
